                            <comment id="12913736" author="rding" created="Wed, 22 Sep 2010 20:39:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hadoop counters are not available in local mode (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1286&quot; title=&quot;Counters are broken in local mode (number of bytes written/number of records written)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1286&quot;&gt;PIG-1286&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So for now I propose that, in local mode,  Pig stats output is changed to something like the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; 
Job Stats (time in seconds):
JobId  Alias Feature Outputs
job_local_0001 raw MAP_ONLY
job_local_0002 rank_sort SAMPLER
job_local_0003 rank_sort ORDER_BY Processed/user_visits_table,

Input(s):
Successfully read records from: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Data/Raw/UserVisits.dat&quot;&lt;/span&gt;

Output(s):
Successfully stored records in: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Processed/user_visits_table&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915408" author="ashutoshc" created="Mon, 27 Sep 2010 19:15:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Tested manually for local mode. Messages were same as proposed above. +1 for the commit. One minor suggestion is to put a line at the start saying something like: &quot;Detected Local mode. Stats reported below may be incomplete.&quot; This will reinforce the message to users that stats reporting is not transparent across different modes (local Vs map-reduce).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12915451" author="rding" created="Mon, 27 Sep 2010 20:57:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to both trunk and 0.8 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
